Dear Brian, Pedro, Attila, & all--

Depending on the specifics of your data and question, another approach that might be appropriate is partitioning dissimilarities, based on Marti Anderson's work with Legendre & McArdle.  The vegan packages has at least 2 functions that implement variations on this approach: adonis2 and varpart  The issue of high compositional turnover Attila mentioned can preclude partitioning of dissimilarity: dissimilarities can't go beyond 1 no matter how many complete turnovers of species occur along a gradient.

Tom


